<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,385,1413,1440]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Ambrysus signoreti</emphasis>
Stål
</taxonomicName>
species complex
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1485,1620]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">
<bibRefCitation author="Usinger, R. L." box="[151,321,1485,1512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="185 - 210" refId="ref12822" refString="Usinger, R. L. (1946) Notes and descriptions of Ambrysus Stal with an account of the life history of Ambrysus mormon Montd. (Hemiptera, Naucoridae). The University of Kansas Sciences Bulletin, 31, 185 - 210." type="journal article" year="1946">Usinger (1946)</bibRefCitation>
first made reference to the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[636,735,1486,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Ambrysus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signoreti">
<emphasis box="[636,735,1486,1511]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">signoreti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” complex when he described 16 new species in 
<emphasis box="[1271,1389,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1861" box="[1271,1385,1485,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Ambrysus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ambrysus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In a later work, 
<bibRefCitation author="La Rivers, I." box="[277,467,1520,1547]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="232 - 237" refId="ref12291" refString="La Rivers, I. (1957) A new Ambrysus from Mexico (Hemiptera, Naucoridae). Entomological News, 68, 232 - 237." type="journal article" year="1957">La Rivers (1957)</bibRefCitation>
listed the unifying features of species in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1861" box="[959,1089,1521,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Ambrysus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signoreti">
<emphasis box="[959,1089,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">A. signoreti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex: 1) broad body shape, 2) wide embolia, 3) prominent maculation, and 4) posterolateral corners of abdominal segments III–V produced (spinose).
</paragraph>
